Direct connection stringPlan: Fix Supabase Sync — Offline Popup Root Cause
The app shows "Offline" in the sidebar and error toasts because of 5 cascading failures in the Supabase integration chain. The database schema, RLS policies, and functions are all correctly deployed — but the app can never reach them.

Root Causes Found (via MCP inspection + code review)
1. No .env file — Supabase client connects to a placeholder

Only .env.example exists with VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here
supabaseClient.ts falls back to https://placeholder.supabase.co + placeholder-key
Every Supabase query silently fails → syncDown() returns null → triggers "Offline Mode" toast
2. No company data exists in the database

MCP confirmed: companies = 0 rows, company_members = 0 rows, company_settings = 0 rows
2 auth users exist but neither has a company → get_user_company_id() returns NULL → RLS blocks everything
3. Edge functions not deployed

create-company and invite-crew exist as code in functions but mcp_supabase_list_edge_functions returns empty → signup can't create a company → new users are stuck
4. Entry point loads the OLD app — new auth system is never used

index.tsx imports root App.tsx which renders SprayFoamCalculator directly
The new App.tsx with AuthProvider, AppShell, AppRouter is never loaded
The "Offline" text the user sees comes from Layout.tsx:226: syncStatus === 'error' && 'Offline'
5. syncDown() doesn't check isSupabaseConfigured before querying

supabaseClient.ts exports isSupabaseConfigured but api.ts never checks it → fires queries against the placeholder URL → fails → user sees "offline"
